===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{zh-ref|Ji Xusheng, 2004}}: {{liushu|i}}: a person ([[人]]) bathing in warm water (now written [[囗]]) in a container ([[皿]]) full of warm water — original form of {{och-l|溫}}. See also [[攸]].

Alternatively, according to Xu Shen, an {{Han compound|囚|t1=prisoner|皿|t2=dish|ls=ic|nocap=y}} – [[feeding]] a [[prisoner]] from a dish. However, the shape in the oracle bones is different.

